parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause sudden near-complete brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Metallic noise when depressing the brake pedal
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of brake rotors can cause uneven brake pad wear, pulsing brake sensation, and reduced braking capability, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
Failure of the front brake caliper can cause brake overheating, reduced braking capability, violent shaking upon brake application, and near fire, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
Failure of the ABS system can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, or skidding, leading to injuries or fatalities.
Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: vehicle jumps out of park into drive
transmission pops out of overdrive into drive
transmission locks up in park and reverse
transmission will not go into reverse and jumps gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Drivetrain failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: causing rear tire to fall off
driveshaft fell off from under the car
causing speedometer to register wrong speed
and odometer to register incorrect mileage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission cooling system failure can cause the transmission to overheat, leading to premature wear and failure.
symptoms: Automatic transmission coolant lines connectors failed

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Differential failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The sudden lockup of the steering wheel can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: the keys get stuck in the steering wheel
the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.

the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front end alignment can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag can cause injuries and fatalities in the event of an accident.
The failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupant is not provided with the necessary protection.
symptoms: The airbag does not deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the impact

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of the airbag can cause injuries, distractions, and accidents, especially if it occurs while the vehicle is in motion.
The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to the failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash, or the unintended deployment of the airbag, resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag light appears on the dashboard
the cruise control fails to work
or the clock spring needs to be replaced.
